00:00:29.265 --> 00:00:31.200
I'm going to scroll down here.

00:00:31.200 --> 00:00:34.350
When I scroll, you can see
that these textblock scales

00:00:34.350 --> 00:00:37.594
now as I scroll down
these elements,

00:00:37.594 --> 00:00:40.295
this image and this
textblock fading.

00:00:40.295 --> 00:00:42.890
So these are the kinds
of animation that make

00:00:42.890 --> 00:00:45.559
a difference when it
comes to web development,

00:00:45.559 --> 00:00:48.260
building a responsive
website is one thing,

00:00:48.260 --> 00:00:51.260
but making it look more
interesting is another thing.

00:00:51.260 --> 00:00:54.574
By adding interactions and
animations to our website,

00:00:54.574 --> 00:00:56.810
we can improve the
user experience and

00:00:56.810 --> 00:01:00.169
our users will enjoy
interacting with our product.

00:01:00.169 --> 00:01:02.945
So let me show you how
interactions work on Webflow.

00:01:02.945 --> 00:01:04.610
When it comes to interactions,

00:01:04.610 --> 00:01:07.205
we have two main
components to work with,

00:01:07.205 --> 00:01:09.500
the trigger and the animation.

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:11.120
So what's the trigger?

00:01:11.120 --> 00:01:14.300
A trigger is something that
triggers the animation.

00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:16.925
In simple words, when
something happens,

00:01:16.925 --> 00:01:18.485
another thing should happen.

00:01:18.485 --> 00:01:22.265
So e.g. if a button is
clicked, it should grow.

00:01:22.265 --> 00:01:23.840
If the user hovers over

00:01:23.840 --> 00:01:26.135
something and other
objects should move.

00:01:26.135 --> 00:01:28.925
In general, we have
two kinds of triggers.

00:01:28.925 --> 00:01:30.440
We have the element trickier,

00:01:30.440 --> 00:01:32.465
and we have the page trigger.

00:01:32.465 --> 00:01:34.055
Let me show you how it works.

00:01:34.055 --> 00:01:36.485
If I head over to the
interactions panel

00:01:36.485 --> 00:01:37.895
on the right side here,

00:01:37.895 --> 00:01:40.595
as you can see there is
this thunderbolt icon.

00:01:40.595 --> 00:01:41.870
I'm going to click on that.

00:01:41.870 --> 00:01:44.135
Here is where we can
create a trigger.

00:01:44.135 --> 00:01:45.200
As I mentioned before,

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:46.850
we have the element trickier

00:01:46.850 --> 00:01:48.530
and we have the page trigger.

00:01:48.530 --> 00:01:50.030
Well, what's the
difference between

00:01:50.030 --> 00:01:52.220
the elementary year
and the page trigger?

00:01:52.220 --> 00:01:53.705
We use the element trigger.

00:01:53.705 --> 00:01:56.030
When the trigger is
an element, e.g. a.

00:01:56.030 --> 00:02:00.485
Button, an image, a text
block heading, anything.

00:02:00.485 --> 00:02:02.360
We can select our elements and

00:02:02.360 --> 00:02:04.550
then we can create
these elements trigger,

00:02:04.550 --> 00:02:07.310
and when the user interacts
with that element,

00:02:07.310 --> 00:02:09.110
it triggers our animation.

00:02:09.110 --> 00:02:10.910
But what about page trigger?

00:02:10.910 --> 00:02:12.935
Well, the page trigger triggers

00:02:12.935 --> 00:02:17.240
our animation when our page
state is changed, e.g.

00:02:17.240 --> 00:02:19.655
if I click on this plus icon,

00:02:19.655 --> 00:02:22.805
you can see we have
mouse move in, viewport,

00:02:22.805 --> 00:02:26.645
wild pages scrolling,
page, load, page scrolled.

00:02:26.645 --> 00:02:28.700
In this case, we don't
need to click on something

00:02:28.700 --> 00:02:30.785
or interact with any element.

00:02:30.785 --> 00:02:33.410
The trigger is our page itself,

00:02:33.410 --> 00:02:36.575
so we can specify when the
page is loaded completely.

00:02:36.575 --> 00:02:39.290
Then play this
particular animation.

00:02:39.290 --> 00:02:41.105
Let me show you
some examples here.

00:02:41.105 --> 00:02:43.925
As you can see here, I
have some simple elements.

00:02:43.925 --> 00:02:46.265
I have a circle, I have
a square root here.

00:02:46.265 --> 00:02:48.650
I'm going to preview this
and I'm going to show you

00:02:48.650 --> 00:02:51.485
some examples of the
element trigger.

00:02:51.485 --> 00:02:55.145
Here. This circle
is our trigger.

00:02:55.145 --> 00:02:57.575
I already created an
interaction for that.

00:02:57.575 --> 00:03:00.035
And when I click on it,
something should happen.

00:03:00.035 --> 00:03:02.195
You need to keep in
mind that the trigger

00:03:02.195 --> 00:03:04.609
shouldn't always animate itself.

00:03:04.609 --> 00:03:06.815
So if I click on this circle,

00:03:06.815 --> 00:03:10.519
the animation shouldn't
necessarily occur on this object.

00:03:10.519 --> 00:03:12.875
I can set a trigger
on this object,

00:03:12.875 --> 00:03:15.350
and I can make other
elements animate,

00:03:15.350 --> 00:03:18.395
like in this case, if I
click on this circle,

00:03:18.395 --> 00:03:19.790
this square should move to

00:03:19.790 --> 00:03:21.830
the right side. Let me show you.

00:03:21.830 --> 00:03:23.540
There we go. So in this case,

